## Automation & Deployment
- Use Makefile targets for all build, deploy, and maintenance tasks.
- Use Docker Compose for local and production orchestration.
- Use Caddy as the reverse proxy and SSL provider.
- Use Trivy for vulnerability scanning of Docker images.
- Use `make deploy` for CI/CD: git pull, build, restart.
- Use non-root users in Docker for security.

## Best Practices
- Write reusable, modular components.
- Keep all secrets and credentials out of source code.
- Document all public functions and exported types.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Write clear commit messages in English.

## Example Tasks for Copilot
- Scaffold new Next.js API routes or pages.
- Generate Docker Compose service definitions.
- Write Makefile targets for new automation needs.
- Suggest Trivy scan scripts for new images.
- Refactor React components to use hooks.
- Add TailwindCSS utility classes for design.
- Write unit tests for API handlers or utilities.
- Suggest secure Dockerfile improvements.

## Output Format
- Use TypeScript for all code unless otherwise specified.
- Use Markdown code blocks with language tags.
- For Makefile or shell scripts, use `makefile` or `bash` tags.
- Add file path comments when modifying or creating files.

## Language
- All code and comments in English.
- User-facing UI text may be in English or Traditional Chinese as appropriate.

# End of .copilot
